The Telegraph - Calcutta : Sports

 Umrigar in hospital again

Mumbai: Former India captain Polly Umrigar has been readmitted to Bombay Hospial on Tuesday for further treatment after having been diagnosed with Non-Hodgkins Lymphoma, a type of cancer that affects bodys immune system. 

Umrigar was readmitted to the hospital ward for another chemotherapy session which he underwent today, said hospital spokesperson Dr Ashish Tiwari. 

Umrigar was admitted to the same hospital earlier this month and kept in the ICU for four days. 

